Channel attribute intentionally omitted — writing Channel="Current" on ProPlus2021Retail triggers a full reinstall instead of reconcile.

Reconcile semantics (gotcha): <Add>+<ExcludeApp> with /configure treats any app NOT in ExcludeApp as "should be installed and is missing" and reinstalls it. So every prior exclusion (Outlook/Publisher/Access from earlier) must stay in the list each run, or it gets pulled back.

Pre-flight:
  - Shell elevated: True
  - Office processes running: only OfficeClickToRun (service host, not user apps)
  - Stop-Service ClickToRunSvc -Force  -> Stopped
  - Start-Service ClickToRunSvc (post-configure) -> Running

Command:
  cd D:\ODT
  .\setup.exe /configure remove-teams.xml
  exit 0

